# {{PROJECT_NAME}} Engineering Rules

These rules are NON-NEGOTIABLE and OVERRIDE any conflicting default behavior.
They are enforced both socially (this document) and mechanically (PHPStan level
7, the Pest architecture suite in `tests/Arch`, and the Stop quality-gate hook
from `mohamed-ashraf-elsaed/claude-kit`).

> Scaffolded by [`mohamed-ashraf-elsaed/claude-kit`](https://packagist.org/packages/mohamed-ashraf-elsaed/claude-kit).
> Sections marked `TODO` are placeholders — fill them in with your project's
> specifics, then delete this note.

## 1. How you must work (mindset)

- **Never over-engineer.** Build the smallest correct thing that satisfies the
  stated requirement. No speculative abstraction, no "framework for the future",
  no patterns added "just in case". If a requirement is not stated, it does not
  exist yet.
- **Simple and readable above all.** Prefer the most straightforward solution a
  new developer could read top-to-bottom and understand. Clarity beats
  cleverness. Short methods, intention-revealing names, early returns, no
  needless indirection.
- **Follow SOLID.** Single responsibility per class/method; depend on
  abstractions at boundaries, not concretions; small, focused interfaces. SOLID
  serves readability — it is never an excuse to over-engineer.
- **Never assume.** Do not guess file paths, column names, API shapes, or
  package behavior. Verify against the actual code, database schema, or official
  docs before acting.
- **Always ask.** When a decision is genuinely ambiguous or has consequential
  trade-offs (data model, dependency, breaking change, irreversible action),
  stop and ask rather than picking a path silently.
- **Validate everything — logically and technically.** Every change must be
  reasoned through AND proven (tests pass, PHPStan is clean, coverage holds). A
  change is not "done" until it is verified.

## 2. Architecture: MVC + Service layer + Data objects

Strict separation of concerns. Each layer has ONE job:

- **Controllers** (`app/Http/Controllers`) — thin. Accept a validated request,
  delegate to a Service or Action, return a response. NO business logic, NO
  direct DB/Eloquent queries, NO data shaping beyond passing DTOs.
- **Form Requests** (`app/Http/Requests`) — all input validation lives here.
- **Services** (`app/Services`) — business logic and orchestration. `final`
  classes, suffixed `Service`. Stateless where possible; injected via the
  container with **constructor dependency injection** (never `app()`/`resolve()`
  inside the class).
- **Actions** (`app/Actions`) — single-purpose units of work. `final`, suffixed
  `Action`, with **exactly one public `__invoke()` method**.
- **Data Objects** (`app/Data`) — immutable, hard-typed DTOs that move data
  between layers. `final readonly` classes, suffixed `Data`. NO behavior beyond
  construction/transformation. Prefer these over passing arrays.
- **Models** (`app/Models`) — persistence + relationships + casts only. No
  business logic.
- **Contracts** (`app/Contracts`) — interfaces for swappable collaborators at
  system boundaries. Depend on the interface, bind the concrete `final`
  implementation in a service provider.

## 3. Hard typing (enforced)

- Every PHP file declares `declare(strict_types=1);`.
- Every parameter, property, and return value is explicitly typed. No untyped
  arrays where a DTO fits; document array shapes in PHPDoc when unavoidable.
- PHPStan (Larastan) runs at **level 7** with **`phpstan-strict-rules`** and
  MUST report **zero** errors.
- Enable Eloquent strict mode (`Model::shouldBeStrict()`); never rely on lazy
  loading or silently-discarded attributes.

## 4. Testing, coverage & the quality gate (enforced)

- Tests are written in **Pest**. Most are feature tests.
- Code coverage must be **≥ 80%** (`--min=80`). New code ships with tests.
- **One shared gate, three places.** `vendor/mohamed-ashraf-elsaed/claude-kit/runtime/quality-checks.sh`
  is the single source of truth and runs the full suite — PHP (Pint, PHPStan
  level 7 + strict-rules, Pest + 80% coverage) and any configured frontend
  checks. It is invoked by the local git pre-commit hook, Claude's Stop hook,
  and CI.
- Coverage requires the `pcov` (or Xdebug) PHP extension; without it the gate
  warns instead of blocking on coverage only.

